## 10. Code structure

A new eval-layer script at `scratch/substrate_fingerprint_atlas.py`:

- `compute_fingerprint(fixture_spec, variant: str = "A") -> dict` — assembles the 12-slot vector from existing tools or existing artifacts.
- `compute_distinguishability_matrix(fingerprints) -> ndarray` — pairwise slot-disagreement count.
- `route_invariance(variant_A, variant_B) -> dict` — per-slot match check.
- `minimum_distinguishing_subset(fingerprints) -> list` — greedy or brute-force slot subset selection.
- `compactness_audit(fingerprint) -> dict` — byte budget verification.
- `main()` — runs all 6 fixtures × 2 variants, aggregates, writes artifact.

Each fixture is defined by a small spec dict (β-grid + slot-source pointers) checked into the script. No new substrate code; no new probe machinery; only eval-layer assembly.

